Two guesthouses have been evacuated over the weekend as a result of the blaze. CAPE TOWN - A fire that raged outside Bredasdorp in the Western Cape has been brought under control. Two guesthouses have been evacuated over the weekend as a result of the blaze. Overberg fire chief Reinard Geldenhuys says the situation is being monitored for any flare-ups. Yesterday afternoon we had some flare-up flames which we managed to work out and everything is out and being monitored. 